body: Supports break, continue, return and with gil blocks in parallel sections.

commit.message: Support break/continue/return in parallel and prange, ready for exceptions
Fix a little bug for break/continue in parallel sections
Use a switch like try/finally for parallel break/continue/return/error
Initialize threads when cython.parallel is imported
Add documentation for break/continue/return/exceptions in parallel blocks
Privatize temporaries and make assignment to __pyx_r critical
Issue comment only when applicable, set __pyx_parallel_why omp shared

Allocate thread-state for each OpenMP thread
Save exc_info in parallel section and re-raise outside in master thread
Disable & fork test with libgomp failure

title: OpenMP exceptions
